# Explicit branching for readability

When controller/service logic has 3+ decision paths (or one path will soon become 3+), prefer explicit `if / else if / else` branching over nested ternaries or compressed expressions.

## Why

- The control flow is easier to scan.
- Future branches can be inserted safely (for example, adding `loadMapping` later).
- The "why this branch runs" remains obvious in code review.

## Guideline

- Use one clearly named variable per user intent (for example `rememberLastMapping`).
- Branch in business-order, not clever-expression order.
- Duplicate a short call in two branches if it keeps flow obvious.

## Example

Prefer:

```groovy
Map model
if (resetToBaseline) {
    model = occurrenceImportService.getDefaultMapping(cmd.importToken, user.tenantId, cmd.encoding, cmd.delimiter)
} else if (rememberLastMapping) {
    model = occurrenceImportService.getMapping(cmd.importToken, user.tenantId, cmd.encoding, cmd.delimiter, user)
} else {
    model = occurrenceImportService.getDefaultMapping(cmd.importToken, user.tenantId, cmd.encoding, cmd.delimiter)
}
```

Over nested ternaries for multi-branch flow.
